<br>
I have read through the Call and Charter and am pleased that you have established your guild on helping others.  What you say about kindness being infectious is true.  I have received much help in my short life on Norath and in return feel obligated to pass along what I can offer to others.<br>
<br>
I have been looking for a guild that would suit me for some time.  Recently my friend, and new member, Emerest recommended your guild to me and I am intrigued.  I feel by treating everyone as an equal and the requirement of the fledgling quest that Random Acts demands an inherent level of maturity that other guilds do not.  I also like the fact that Random Acts has regularly organized events lending a greater sense of community.<br>
<br>
Emerest has been a great help in directing me to information on Random Acts.  I think she would make a great sponsor but also know she is too new to the guild to allowed such a task.  Regardless she has invited me to accompany her to some of the anniversary events next week and I look forward to meeting more members. I am unsure though if that isn’t just to make sure she doesn’t get lost. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I thank you for your consideration and look forward to hearing from you.<br>
<br>
Turgut Pyrocast<br>
23rd Erudian Wizard <br>
